cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on deep metric learning in computer vision, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a framework for updating the model using a mini-batch of data, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper uses distributionally robust optimization to formulate a loss function, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. The empirical studies are conducted on benchmark datasets, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible sub-categories.
